OL,3,CFormer Glamorgan and England batter
OL,4,Cand ECB boss Hugh Morris dies aged 62
OL,6,FHugh Morris, the former England and
OL,7,FGlamorgan batter who went on to hold
OL,8,Fsenior positions with both country and
OL,9,Fcounty, has died aged 62.
OL,11,FMorris became Glamorgan's youngest
OL,12,Fever captain aged 22 before returning
OL,13,Fto the role later in his career,
OL,14,Fleading them to the Sunday League
OL,15,Ftitle in 1993, their first trophy in
OL,16,F24 years.
OL,18,FAfter ending a 17-year playing career
OL,19,Fin 1997 Morris had a series of off-
OL,20,Ffield roles at the England and Wales
OL,21,FCricket Board.
